---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import Nav from '../components/Nav.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import { site } from '../config/site';
import '../styles/legal.css';

const lastUpdated = 'June 5, 2026';
---

<Base
  title="Privacy Policy | Freedom with AI"
  description="How Freedom with AI collects, uses, and protects your information."
>
  <Nav />
  <main id="main-content" class="container legal-page">
    <div class="legal-page__inner">
      <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="legal-page__updated">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>

      <p class="legal-page__lede">
        {site.brand} (&ldquo;{site.brand},&rdquo; &ldquo;we,&rdquo; &ldquo;us,&rdquo; or
        &ldquo;our&rdquo;) respects your privacy. This policy explains what we collect when
        you use <strong>freedomwith.ai</strong>, how we use it, and the choices you have.
      </p>

      <h2>Scope</h2>
      <p>
        This policy covers the <strong>freedomwith.ai</strong> website and the ways you can
        reach us through it. Our product, <a href={site.faibuddyUrl} target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">faibuddy</a>,
        is a separate service governed by its own terms and privacy policy. Third-party
        platforms we link to (such as YouTube, X, and LinkedIn) have their own policies.
      </p>

      <h2>Information we collect</h2>
      <h3>Information you give us</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>When you contact or apply to work with us:</strong> your name, email
          address, what best describes your situation, what you want to be different and why
          now, and any optional link you choose to share.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>When you join our list:</strong> your email address, so we can send field
          notes, new videos, and event updates you ask for.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Information collected automatically</h3>
      <p>
        Like most websites, we and our service providers may collect basic technical and
        usage data, such as your browser type, device, approximate location (from your IP
        address), pages viewed, and referring links. This may involve cookies or similar
        technologies used for analytics and security. Where required, we ask for your
        consent first.
      </p>

      <h2>How we use your information</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>To respond to your message and assess whether advisory is a good fit.</li>
        <li>To send updates, content, and event news you have opted into.</li>
        <li>To operate, secure, measure, and improve the website.</li>
        <li>To comply with legal obligations and protect our rights.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>How we share information</h2>
      <p>
        We do not sell your personal information. We share it only with trusted service
        providers who help us run the site and communicate with you (for example, hosting,
        email, and analytics providers), and only as needed to perform those services. We
        may also disclose information if required by law or to protect the rights, safety,
        and security of our users and our business.
      </p>

      <h2>Cookies and analytics</h2>
      <p>
        We may use cookies and analytics tools to understand how the site is used so we can
        improve it. You can control cookies through your browser settings, and where we use
        non-essential cookies we will seek your consent. Disabling cookies may affect some
        functionality.
      </p>

      <h2>Data retention</h2>
      <p>
        We keep your information only as long as needed for the purposes described here,
        including to respond to you, provide updates you requested, meet legal requirements,
        and resolve disputes. You can ask us to delete your information at any time.
      </p>

      <h2>Your choices and rights</h2>
      <p>
        Depending on where you live, you may have the right to access, correct, delete, or
        port your personal information, to object to or restrict certain processing, and to
        withdraw consent. You can unsubscribe from emails at any time using the link in any
        message. To exercise any of these rights, <a href="/contact">contact us</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>International users</h2>
      <p>
        We operate from the United States. If you access the site from another country, your
        information may be processed in the United States and other locations with different
        data protection laws than your own.
      </p>

      <h2>Children&rsquo;s privacy</h2>
      <p>
        This site is intended for professionals and is not directed to children. We do not
        knowingly collect personal information from children under 16.
      </p>

      <h2>Changes to this policy</h2>
      <p>
        We may update this policy from time to time. When we do, we will revise the
        &ldquo;Last updated&rdquo; date above. Material changes will be made clear on this
        page.
      </p>

      <div class="legal-page__contact">
        <h2>Contact us</h2>
        <p>
          Questions about this policy or your information? Reach us through our
          <a href="/contact"> contact page</a> and we will respond.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</Base>
